  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations. Validation evidence references the Taskin et al. (2012) benchmark dataset obtained under pump-as-oxygenator recirculation conditions at 3 L/min and 3500 RPM, which overlaps partially with the VAD operating envelope. The Output Comparison credibility factor is assessed as achieved at Gradation 3 against a required Gradation 4, with the shortfall attributed to limited operating-point coverage. All 13 ASME V&V 40 factors are addressed; seven are formally assessed and six are flagged as epistemic gaps. Decision: Accepted pending post-market surveillance commitment.",
